<br>
I suspect you're problem stems from the anti-spam code. You say you're hotkey is (hold, assist, attack). Hold will probably go through, assist get blocked by the spam blocker, and then attack, so you stay on the same target and reattack it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
As far as I can tell from the information here, /pet hold is /pet back off + a hate list locker. While the hate list is locked, the pet won't gain aggro anything. As soon as you attack a mob, the hate list becomes unlocked (so he CAN attack <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ), and normal rules apply.<br>
<br>
The only reason I was disappointed was cos of the way I read it. I was hoping that &quot;until you tell it to attack&quot; would mean that my pet *couldn't* aggro a mob until I told him to attack <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Either way, this is still a very useful skill. I'll be able to use pets in ToV. I'll be able to pull without fear of my pet running off too early cos I got hit. I'll be able to pull my pet away from a mob beating on him. I couldn't do any of these before /pet hold.<br>
<br>
