<br>
/pet back off<br>
/pet back off<br>
<br>
I hit the hotkey 8 or 10 times in 3-7 second intervals and got 4 - 5 &quot;sorry master, calming down&quot; messages.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> My biggest issue is pets switching targets, not pets comming to my defense. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->/pet hold was never intended to fix this problem.  Personally, I suggested, and was hoping for, an adustment to /pet attack so that /pet attack would add a certian amount of hate to the master's target.  This would allow you not only prevent the pets from switching targets, but also would allow you to cause the pet to switch targets.  It wouldn't be perfect, but I think it would be a far better solution than combining /pet hold and /pet attack as you suggest.<br>
<br>
As it is, /pet hold seems to be an excellent ability and one I look forward to attaining.<br>
