<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  /pet hold<br>
pause 10<br>
/pet back off</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
This seems to work like a charm so far.  I thought I might need a new hot key, but it seems to me that every time I would want to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  /pet hold</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, I would want <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  /pet back off</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> as well, and basically vice versa.<br>
<br>
How it appears to work is consistant with the following theory:<br>
<br>
A pet follows its movement mode <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  (guard, sit, follow)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> only when its hate list is empty, or it is held.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  /pet hold</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> causes the pet to ignore its hate list.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  /pet back off</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> causes the pet to empty its hate list.<br>
<br>
Everything I have seen so far fits this theory.  I will play with it some more.<br>
<br>
